{"title": "Don't Be Ridiculous", "content": "\"... dogs come from the Moon, not the Sun!\"\n\nAlice says something ridiculous. Bob responds with this Stock Phrase (or some close relative), then explains why Alice's statement is ridiculous. Of course, Bob's justification is either as absurd, more absurd, or otherwise not a rebuttal one would normally make to the original statement.\n\nOften, Bob is The Ditz, a Cloudcuckoolander, or a Bunny-Ears Lawyer. Less often, Alice is likewise one of those characters.\n\nA common variant is that Alice's original statement was an attempt to guess what Bob is planning or doing. (\"So you're going to just storm the castle?\" \"Don't be absurd. I'm going to storm the castle carrying this marionette. Sheesh.\")\n\nNot quite the same as the usage of the phrase by Funny Foreigner Balki Bartokomous in the sitcom Perfect Strangers. (He would say it when suspected of doing something wrong, but usually wouldn't follow up with a nonsensical rebuttal.)\n\nSee Insane Troll Logic. Somewhat related to Voodoo Shark (when Real Life fiction-creators are seen doing this themselves \u2014 albeit not in response to a theory they find absurd). May also involve Distinction Without a Difference (\"No, I'm not eating an eraser. I'm eating two erasers\"). Compare Worrying for the Wrong Reason (\"Sharks? Don't be silly. The crocodiles will get you first\").", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DontBeRidiculous", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PerfectStrangers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AzumangaDaioh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/GAGeijutsukaArtDesignClass", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/AliceInWonderland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MuppetTreasureIsland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BryonyAndRoses", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CharlieAndTheChocolateFactory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheHitchhikersGuideToTheGalaxy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SoLongAndThanksForAllTheFish", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/TheImportanceOfBeingEarnest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RiversOfLondon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RAMacAvoy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Fringe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FullHouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MontyPythonsFlyingCircus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ShakeItUp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TwoAndAHalfMen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/TheGoonShow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Spamalot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DragonAgeOriginsAwakening", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/DarthsAndDroids", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheOrderOfTheStick", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Anastasia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CodenameKidsNextDoor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DarkwingDuck", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DextersLaboratory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/JusticeLeague", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheQuestion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Squidbillies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TennesseeTuxedoAndHisTales"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StockPhrase", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Cloudcuckoolander", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BunnyEarsLawyer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FunnyForeigner", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InsaneTrollLogic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VoodooShark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DistinctionWithoutADifference", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorryingForTheWrongReason", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LogicalFallacies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SantaClaus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoesLaw", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EskimosArentReal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicStrip/Peanuts", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConsultingMisterPuppet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWonka", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/Jingo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/DoctorWhoS29E11Utopia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main